        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Was playing with the new Hitsmode functionality last night, and I really like it.  How I set it up was others hits in one window, enrage/rampage/ds/crit(melee/caster)/non-melee in another and left my hits/getting hit in my main window with chats, faction info, and everything else.  I locked down the two new windows and made them 100% transparent always.  It worked out pretty well and got interesting results.  Best one was they became bascially like the old hitsmode windows, but scrollable, which is sometimes useful.  I could then use the chat options to turn stuff on and off for raid situations.  Some wierd stuff happened though.</P><P>When I tapped, for example, I saw I was casting in chat window, damage went into my second window and healing was in my chat window.  Pet taunting was in chat window as well, but didn't see it too much, so it wasn't a big deal.  Of course, last night I was running in 8 chat channels, so chat spam was a bit heavy, even by my standards (normally run 6 plus raid stuff).  Going to continue experimenting with them to get them a bit better, but thus far the UI is really a lot of fun to customize.  I'm using mods from all over and then changing them to make my interface more "me".</P><P><i><b><font color=gold><font size=4>Dinomight Questaholic</b></font id=size4><BR>Master of the Lizard Dance on Test  {The Grove}</i></font id=gold><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
